CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, National Edition, September 5, 1942, pg. 15 reads: "Winners Of "Double V" Beauty Pageant - The above beauties were prize winners at the first annual "Double V" Water and Beauty Pageant held last Friday at the Ammon pool, Pittsburgh. From left to right; Miss Myrtle Gilkes, third place; Miss Vivian Wrenn, second, and Miss Frances ...ever, first prize winner.  The contest was sponsored by the Ammon Recreation Center, the Crawford Art Center and The Pittsburgh Courier. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Winners of Double V Water and Beauty Pageant, Myrtle Gilkes, Vivian Wrenn, and Frances Weaver, wearing bathing suits, posed in interior in front of dark curtains
